        <p>The Guinness World Record for the longest duration in the dead hang position is <strong>80 minutes and 41 seconds</strong>. Kenta Adachi of Japan set this record on 18 November 2022 in Shunan, Yamaguchi. Adachi is a coast guard navigator and diver who also holds the Guinness record for the most consecutive pull-ups, with 651.</p>
        <p>Adachi hung from a horizontal bar with his feet off the ground for the entire attempt. His hands stayed on the bar without repositioning. The attempt was filmed, witnessed and verified by Guinness adjudicators. He broke the previous record of 16 minutes 3 seconds, set by Harald Riise of Norway on 7 November 2020.</p>
        <p>To understand the scale of this achievement: the average untrained adult hangs for 30-60 seconds. Adachi held for more than 80 minutes, over 100 times longer than the average person's maximum effort.</p>

        <div class="callout">
          <p><strong>Record rules:</strong> The Guinness dead hang record requires a full bodyweight hang from a horizontal bar. Both feet must leave the ground completely. No kipping, swinging or repositioning of the hands. The timer stops when any part of the body contacts the ground or the athlete releases the bar.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="male-records">Men's Dead Hang Records</h2>
        <p>Competitive dead hanging has grown rapidly. The following table lists the verified holders of the Guinness "Longest duration in the dead hang position (male)" record and the times that preceded the current mark.</p>

        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Athlete</th>
              <th>Country</th>
              <th>Time</th>
              <th>Year</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Kenta Adachi</strong></td><td>Japan</td><td>80:41</td><td>2022</td><td>Current Guinness World Record</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Harald Riise</td><td>Norway</td><td>16:03</td><td>2020</td><td>Previous record holder</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tazio Gavioli</td><td>Italy</td><td>13:52</td><td>2018</td><td>Former record holder</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>The men's record progressed steadily and then jumped dramatically. Tazio Gavioli held 13 minutes 52 seconds in 2018, Harald Riise extended it to 16 minutes 3 seconds in 2020, and Kenta Adachi then set a new mark of 80 minutes 41 seconds in 2022, more than four times the previous record.</p>

        <h2 id="female-records">Women's Dead Hang Records</h2>
        <p><strong>Guinness does not list an open female duration record for the dead hang.</strong> The headline category, "Longest duration in the dead hang position", is a male category, currently held by Kenta Adachi. The female dead hang record Guinness does verify is an age title: oldest person to hold the dead hang position (female).</p>
        <p>That title belongs to <strong>Ann Crile Esselstyn</strong> of the USA, who held a dead hang for <strong>2 minutes 52 seconds</strong> at the age of 90 years and 231 days on 6 March 2026. She took it from Annie Judis of the USA, who set the record in 2024 at the age of 81.</p>

        <table class="data-table">
