        <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>What is the world record for a dead hang?</h3>
          <p>The Guinness World Record for the longest duration in the dead hang position is 80 minutes and 41 seconds, set by Kenta Adachi of Japan on 18 November 2022. He broke the previous record of 16 minutes 3 seconds, set by Harald Riise of Norway on 7 November 2020.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>What is the female dead hang world record?</h3>
          <p>Guinness does not list an open female duration record for the dead hang. The headline category, "Longest duration in the dead hang position", is a male category. The female record Guinness verifies is an age title: oldest person to hold the dead hang position (female), held by Ann Crile Esselstyn of the USA, who hung for 2 minutes 52 seconds at 90 years and 231 days on 6 March 2026.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>Can a normal person hang for 5 minutes?</h3>
          <p>A 5-minute dead hang is extremely difficult. The average untrained adult holds 30-60 seconds. Reaching 5 minutes requires months of dedicated grip training, specific forearm endurance programming and mental conditioning. Fewer than 1% of regular gym-goers achieve this.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>How long can the average person dead hang?</h3>
          <p>The average untrained person dead hangs for 20-40 seconds. Men average 30-60 seconds and women 20-40 seconds. With 4-8 weeks of training, most people reach 60-90 seconds. The world record of over 80 minutes is more than 100 times longer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>Is a 3 minute dead hang impressive?</h3>
          <p>A 3-minute dead hang is impressive by any standard. This places you well above 95% of the general population. Most trained gym-goers never reach 3 minutes. It requires dedicated forearm endurance training beyond general fitness work.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>Who holds the dead hang world record?</h3>
          <p>Kenta Adachi of Japan holds the dead hang world record at 80 minutes 41 seconds, set on 18 November 2022. He also holds the Guinness record for the most consecutive pull-ups, with 651.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>What is the world record for hanging on a bar?</h3>
          <p>The record for hanging on a bar in the dead hang position is 80 minutes 41 seconds, set by Kenta Adachi of Japan in 2022 and verified by Guinness World Records. It is the same category often searched as the longest dead hang.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
          <h3>What is the longest time hanging from a bar?</h3>
          <p>The longest verified time hanging from a bar in a dead hang is 80 minutes 41 seconds by Kenta Adachi of Japan in 2022. The previous record was 16 minutes 3 seconds by Harald Riise of Norway.</p>
        </div>

